{
  "texts": [
    "In clinical settings, AI/ML algorithms can quickly manage huge amounts of data, enabling efficient pain assessment and decision-making.",
    "This saves time for healthcare providers, allowing them to focus on treatment planning and patient care.",
    "It also frees up healthcare providers' time to focus on patient care rather than searching or entering information [15,32].Technologically advanced hospitals are now exploring the use of AI technologies to help improve the accuracy of practice [115] and lower the cost of operations by presenting detailed information on various treatment options [115,116].Personalized Approach AI models can consider individual patient characteristics, genetic factors, medical records, and imaging to tailor personalized pain assessment and management strategies.",
    "This strategy can improve treatment outcomes and patient satisfaction.",
    "Another benefit of ML in the healthcare business is giving individualized therapies that are more dynamic and efficient by combining personal health with predictive analytics [103,104]."
  ]
}